        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Many projects aim to prevent or slow this loss by revitalizing ([[language revitalization]]) endangered languages and promoting education and literacy in minority languages. Across the world, many countries have enacted specific legislation ([[Language policy]]) to protect and stabilize the language of indigenous speech communities ([[speech community]]). A minority of linguists have argued that language loss is a natural process that should not be counteracted, and that documenting endangered languages for posterity is sufficient."
